# Monorepo Package Boundaries

## Package Dependency Order

Packages form a strict DAG — lower packages must NOT import from higher ones:

```
@excalidraw/common        ← no internal deps
       ↓
@excalidraw/math          ← may import common
       ↓
@excalidraw/element       ← may import common, math
       ↓
@excalidraw/excalidraw    ← may import common, math, element
       ↓
excalidraw-app            ← may import all packages (not published)
```

- `@excalidraw/common` must remain free of internal cross-package imports.
- `@excalidraw/math` must not import from `element` or `excalidraw`.
- `@excalidraw/element` must not import from `excalidraw` or `excalidraw-app`.
- Circular dependencies between packages are **forbidden**.

## Build Order

Packages must be built in dependency order:

```bash
yarn build:packages   # builds: common → math → element → excalidraw
```

Do not run builds out of order — downstream packages link against the compiled output of their deps.

## Package Responsibilities

| Package | Responsibility |
|---------|---------------|
| `@excalidraw/common` | Constants, pure utilities, shared colors |
| `@excalidraw/math` | 2D vector/matrix/angle primitives (no DOM, no React) |
| `@excalidraw/element` | Element types, geometry, binding, hit testing |
| `@excalidraw/excalidraw` | React component, canvas rendering, actions, state |
| `excalidraw-app` | Deployed web app (PWA, Firebase, collaboration) |

## Rules

- Math utilities belong in `@excalidraw/math` — not duplicated in other packages.
- Element geometry (bounding boxes, hit testing) belongs in `@excalidraw/element`.
- React components and UI belong in `@excalidraw/excalidraw` or `excalidraw-app`.
- Do NOT import `excalidraw-app` code from any published package.

## How to verify

- `yarn test:typecheck` — TypeScript will catch cross-boundary import errors via `tsconfig.json` path aliases.
- `yarn build:packages` — must succeed without errors for all packages in order.
- Check for circular deps: `rg 'from.*@excalidraw/excalidraw' packages/element` should be empty.
